<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870602-0148 </DOCNO><HL> Monsanto Co. to PurchasePart of French Firm's Line</HL><DD> 06/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MTCTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> ST. LOUIS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Monsanto Co. said it agreed to buy some assets of the polyphenyl business of Rhone-Poulenc S.A., of France. Terms weren't disclosed.    Monsanto, a chemical concern, said the purchase includes the French chemical company's heat-transfer-fluid product, which is called Gilotherm TH.    Heat-transfer liquids are used for indirect heating and cooling in chemical processing and synthetic-fiber manufacturing. </TEXT></DOC>